<HEAD>With AM-House-Drugs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 228-182 roll call Thursday by
which the House deleted from a drug bill a provision requiring a
seven-day waiting period for the purchase of handguns, substituting
instead a vaguely defined system for identifying convicted felons
seeking to buy handguns.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to eliminate the waiting period from
the bill.
   Voting yes were 101 Democrats and 127 Republicans.
   Voting no were 137 Democrats and 45 Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
