<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Pinned,0197</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lawyer Pins Would-Be Car Thief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RUPERT, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 140-pound man with a brick who tried to
rob a law office has proven no match for a 280-pound lawyer.
   A man walked into Raymundo Pena's law office Wednesday night,
holding a brick he apparently picked up outside the door, according
to police.
   The robber told Pena he wanted the keys to his car.
   ``I kept trying to get closer to him,'' Pena said. ``He was just
out of range.''
   Pena, who wrestled for his high school and played football in
college, waited until he saw the man fiddling with the keys.
   ``I grabbed his wrist that had the brick in it, hit him in the
chest with my shoulder, then, as he was falling back, I did an
ankle sweep,'' Pena said.
   Pena wrapped matters up with an arm bar and a half nelson.
   His sister-in-law, Tammy Lopez, pitched in by planting her knee
on the robber.
   Police arrived and arrested the pinned man, 24-year-old Ronnie
Cantu of Rupert. Cantu was charged Thursday with aggravated
assault, first-degree robbery and first-degree burglary,
authorities said.
