<HEAD>Weathering Hurricanes Becomes Family Tradition</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Hurricane Gilbert, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BROWNSVILLE, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For Amelia Ochoa and five generations
of relatives, weathering hurricanes has become a family tradition.
   At last count, 22 family members had gathered under the roof of
Mrs. Ochoa's white brick home as wind began to bend palm trees
Thursday.
   ``I think my house is good enough to go through a hurricane, but
I wanted to be with my mother,'' said Oralia Guvman, 41.
