<1ST_LINE>r w PM-Britain-Mail     09-16 0110</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Britain-Mail,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mail Service Restored to Britain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mail service to Great Britain is being
restored today, the U.S. Postal Service announced.
   Postmaster General Anthony M. Frank said he has been advised by
the British Post Office that the strike there has ended, and that
the agency is again accepting mail.
   The U.S. Postal Service embargoed mail to the United Kingdom on
Sept. 7, when authorities in that nation reported that they were
unable to accept incoming mail because of a strike.
   Because of a backlog of mail to be sorted and delivered in Great
Britain, however, Frank cautioned, there may still be some delays
in service.
</TEXT>
