<HEAD>Baby Who Was Godson Of Abortion Foe Dies Of SIDS</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A baby whose mother
credited Premier Bill Vander Zalm with inspiring her not to have an
abortion has died from sudden infant death syndrome, authorities
said.
   The child's mother, Serina Hinde, had asked Vander Zalm to
become the boy's godfather because of his strong views against
abortion. The British Columbia leader agreed and attended the
baptism of the baby, Richard, at a Roman Catholic Church on Aug. 14.
   A coroner's report said Richard died Thursday of sudden infant
death syndrome. He was born on July 3, about six weeks premature.
   When she asked Vander Zalm to be godfather, Ms. Hinde, 26, said
she had seriously considered having an abortion when she found
herself pregnant with a child the father didn't want.
   ``I listened to what (Vander Zalm) had to say,'' she said.
   Earler this year, Vander Zalm tried unsuccessfully to have the
provincial government health insurance program stop paying for
abortions except when a woman's life was endangered by a pregnancy.
