<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Reagan-Trip     09-16 0194</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Reagan-Trip,190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Plans Texas Trip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan will visit the Johnson Space
Center in Houston next week and campaign for Vice President George
Bush at other stops in the hotly contested states of Texas and
Florida, the White House announced today.
   White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said it is ``a
possibility'' that Reagan will appear with presidential aspirant
Bush at a Houston fundraising event Thursday evening.
   Fitzwater said the possible joint appearance in the state Bush
calls home had not yet been ``firmed up.''
   Reagan also is slated to attend a rally at Baylor University in
Waco and appear at a private fundraising event for Beau Boulter,
the Republican congressman from Amarillo who is opposing Sen. Lloyd
Bentsen for his Senate seat, Fitzwater said.
   Even though Bentsen is running for vice president on the
Democratic ticket with Gov. Michael Dukakis, he is allowed under
Texas law to campaign at the same time for reelection to the Senate.
   On Friday, Reagan travels to Fort Lauderdale, Fla., to attend a
brunch sponsored by the state Republican Party, Fitzwater said.
   The president is scheduled to return to Washington later that
same day.
</TEXT>
