<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Hungary-Smuggling,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Court Jails 10 For Smuggling People To West</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Hungarian court sentenced 10 people
to jail for smuggling Romanians and East Germans through Hungary to
the West, the official news agency MTI said Friday.
   It said the group charged up to $11,100 for taking Romanians out
of their country into Hungary, then driving them across Hungary and
smuggling them over the Austrian border.
   For a smaller fee, East Germans who traveled visa-free to
Czechoslovakia were smuggled into Hungary and then across to
Austria, MTI said.
   It said the ring was exposed after Hungarian border guards found
the escapees in trucks at the crossing to Austria.
   MTI said a West German identified only as Siegfried Schwanke
appealed his five-year sentence and had it reduced Thursday to four
years. He will be expelled when the term is served, it said.
   Four Hungarians were sentenced to 2{ years in jail, a fine and
loss of their driving licence for two years, and five unidentified
defendants have begun serving lighter jail terms, MTI said.
