<1ST_LINE>r p AM-GOP-Israel     09-16 0617</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-GOP-Israel,620</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>GOP Congressmen Say Three Democratic Panelists are Anti-Israeli</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of Republican congressmen sought to
defuse charges of anti-semitism in the GOP campaign by charging
Friday that Democratic presidential nominee Michael Dukakis
appointed three ``anti-Israeli, pro-Palestinian'' members to the
party's ruling body.
   Rep. Norman Lent, R-N.Y., said the three objectionable members
were appointed to the 400-member Democratic National Committee
after the pention in Atlanta as a concession to
defeated presidential contender Jesse Jackson.
   ``The presence of (the three) on the Democratic team raises
questions about Michael Dukakis' judgmentarty's July conv and his submission
to
Jesse Jackson,'' Lent told a news conference.
