<HEAD>Man Arrested For Allegedly Threatening Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FINDLAY, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Findlay man sitting in a downtown
restaurant was arrested Friday after someone allegedly overheard
him making threatening remarks against Vice President George Bush,
police said.
   Bush, the Republican presidential nominee, campaigned in the
northwest Ohio city Friday morning.
   Police said Charles T. Rode Jr., 35, allegedly made threatening
