<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Britain-Stocks     09-16 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Down At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British stocks declined by midday Friday but were
heading higher following the government's release of inflation
figures that weren't as bad as some economists had expected.
   The report showed retail prices rose 1.1 percent in August from
July and were up 5.7 percent from a year earlier.
   ``Basically it wasn't a bad figure,'' said Charles Larkum, an
equity market analyst at James Capel and Co. ``The market is in a
vulnerable position at the moment (and) had been nerving itself up
for another bad figure.''
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was down 7.1
points, or 0.4 percent, at 1,762.2 at about 12:30 p.m. London time.
   Volume totaled 269.5 million shares, compared with 243.5 million
shares at the same time Thursday.
</TEXT>
