<1ST_LINE>u f BC-TheWeekAhead     09-16 0353</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-The Week Ahead,0379</2ND_LINE>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the major business events and economic events scheduled
for the coming week (some dates are tentative):
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>MONDAY, Sept. 19</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   WASHINGTON _ The Senate is scheduled to take up the U.S.-Canada
Free Trade Agreement with a vote expected in early evening. The
Senate then plans to resume consideration of the minimum wage bill
and should spend much of the week on it. A bill that would require
employers to give parents time off for childbirth and child illness
is next on the schedule.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>TUESDAY, Sept. 20</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department is to release the final
revision of growth in the gross national product during the second
quarter; due at 8:30 a.m. EDT.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>WEDNESDAY, Sept. 21</BYLINE>
