<HEAD>Apple Unveils New Version Of Apple IIc</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CUPERTINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Apple Computer Inc. is hoping an
updated version of its 12-year-old Apple IIc will sell briskly this
Christmas.
   The new machine is called Apple IIc Plus and is targeted at the
consumer market.
   An Apple IIc Plus with a monochrome monitor will sell for $859,
down from $950 for its predecessor. A color system will cost
$1,099, a drop from $1,203.
   Kevin McDonald, manager of Apple's home education marketing
group, said the price drop resulted from competition in the
consumer market.
   The main features of the Apple IIc Plus include a faster central
processor, allowing it to calculate more quickly; a built-in power
supply that makes the computer more compact and lighter in weight;
and a built-in 3.5-inch disk drive with more capacity than the
earlier 5.25-inch model.
